cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the measurement of research productivity and impact, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely categories as they deal with the organization and retrieval of scientific publications. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a possibility as it deals with the social and ethical implications of technology, which includes the evaluation of research impact. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible categories as they may involve the analysis of citation networks and the evaluation of research impact in those networks.
